section.section:
Whether or not an individual receives compensation for the individual's services, an employee of a county health department or other local department or agency functioning as a school nurse or school health aide or a member of the administrative, educational, or support staff of, or an individual who serves under a contract for services to, any public, private, or parochial school is immune from liability for:
Making a report required by law, if the individual acts on reasonable grounds;
Participating in a judicial proceeding that results from the individual's report; and
Under the influence of alcoholic beverages or a controlled dangerous substance;
In possession of alcoholic beverages or a controlled dangerous substance; or
Involved in the illegal sale or distribution of alcoholic beverages or a controlled dangerous substance.
